00:46.760 --> 00:50.834
JOE: In 1917, I signed up
to fight the Huns in France.

01:02.240 --> 01:04.994
Good men died all around me.

01:05.319 --> 01:07.789
And I saw no reason for it.

01:11.120 --> 01:13.430
The rules we lived by were lies.

01:15.760 --> 01:18.673
And they didn't apply
to those who made them.

01:20.280 --> 01:24.069
I swore if I made it home,
I would never follow orders again.

01:26.560 --> 01:28.313
I left a soldier.

01:29.680 --> 01:31.797
I came home an outlaw.

01:43.320 --> 01:45.710
I lived one robbery to the next.

01:46.720 --> 01:49.030
A good day was filled by sleep,

01:49.200 --> 01:52.591
and a good night spent
running too hard to look back.

01:56.200 --> 02:01.070
I lived that life for 10 years
until it caught up to me.

02:06.080 --> 02:09.073
It all started with an inside man.

02:18.800 --> 02:21.872
The Albert White crew
was playing a high stakes poker game,

02:22.040 --> 02:25.397
and our inside man
left the back door open for us.

02:32.080 --> 02:33.400
Three, two, one.

02:33.560 --> 02:34.994
Give us the fucking money.

02:35.160 --> 02:37.516
- Do you know whose fucking place this is?
- Give it!

02:37.680 --> 02:40.354
I asked, "Do you know whose fucking card
game this is", you fucking dunce?

02:40.520 --> 02:43.240
- You heard of Albert White?
- (GUN COCKS) Keep talking, bimbo.

02:43.480 --> 02:44.994
- (GRUNTS)
- Miss, come here. Come here!

02:46.520 --> 02:48.193
Do you want a drink
to go with your robbery?

02:48.360 --> 02:50.829
No. Just the money. Put it in the bag.

02:51.080 --> 02:53.834
Let's go. In the bag. Right here.
Nice and easy.

02:56.360 --> 02:57.760
What's your name?

02:57.920 --> 03:00.992
Emma Gould. What's yours?

03:01.280 --> 03:03.192
- You're gonna put a sock in my mouth?
- That's right.

03:03.360 --> 03:05.750
A sock? In my mouth?

03:05.960 --> 03:08.680
Never been used before,
and I wouldn't lie to you.

03:08.840 --> 03:10.274
That's what all the liars say.

03:10.440 --> 03:11.954
Quick, open up.

03:14.480 --> 03:16.631
Just do a quick...

03:16.840 --> 03:17.956
MAN: Watch this guy.

03:18.120 --> 03:19.395
Here we go.

03:19.560 --> 03:21.472
MAN: Hey, put your fucking hands
on the table.

03:21.680 --> 03:22.716
Great.

03:23.840 --> 03:26.355
All right, boys. Let's go.

03:27.760 --> 03:29.638
You've got some balls.

03:30.920 --> 03:33.674
- (CAR HONKS)
- (TIRES SCREECH)

03:34.000 --> 03:35.832
Just slow down and stop driving
like we did something.

03:36.000 --> 03:37.229
Relax.

03:37.440 --> 03:39.796
We made out pretty good.
It was a nice hit.

03:39.960 --> 03:41.519
Yeah, it's all mine.

03:41.680 --> 03:42.909
JOE: Yeah. It's a living.

03:43.080 --> 03:46.357
- Yeah, you fucking Mick.
- Get the fuck out of here. Drive the car.

03:54.080 --> 03:57.437
ALBERT: Good afternoon. I'm Albert White.

04:00.840 --> 04:02.433
You must be Joe.

04:03.000 --> 04:03.990
Coughlin.

04:04.160 --> 04:06.470
Good to put a face to the name.

04:06.760 --> 04:08.752
This is Brennan Loomis, friend of mine.

04:08.920 --> 04:09.956
How are you?

04:12.800 --> 04:16.476
You're too smart
for the stuff you've been pulling.

04:16.800 --> 04:19.599
Nickel and diming with two dumb Guineas.

04:19.760 --> 04:23.231
They're your friends,
but they're stupid and they're wops.

04:23.400 --> 04:25.198
And they won't live to see 40.

04:29.560 --> 04:31.870
Take your time.

04:32.200 --> 04:34.510
But you can't work on your own.

04:36.480 --> 04:38.870
Not in this town.

04:39.200 --> 04:41.192
JOE: Albert was rounding up the troops.

04:41.640 --> 04:44.758
There was a war going on over rum.

04:44.920 --> 04:46.513
Dermot, go and have a word.

04:46.720 --> 04:48.473
JOE: Albert White ran the Irish mob...

04:48.680 --> 04:51.752
Brennan, keep an eye on him.

04:52.680 --> 04:53.830
Uh-huh.

04:54.080 --> 04:57.073
...and Maso Pescatore ran the Italians.

04:57.920 --> 04:59.798
It was tit for tat.

05:00.880 --> 05:02.394
- (WOMAN SCREAMS)
- (MAN GASPS)

05:05.920 --> 05:08.754
The deadliest year
in the history of Boston.

05:08.920 --> 05:09.910
(SCREAMING)

05:10.360 --> 05:11.714
(CAR TIRES SCREECH)

05:15.520 --> 05:18.592
White's gang set fire to rum trucks.

05:18.760 --> 05:20.513
Then a guy on Maso's payroll

05:20.680 --> 05:23.434
went home with a girl
no one had seen before.

05:23.600 --> 05:25.080
(GRUNTING)

05:28.640 --> 05:30.916
No winner. Just a lot of mess.

05:31.080 --> 05:33.151
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

05:37.760 --> 05:41.436
I wanted nothing to do
with Albert White and his war.

05:41.680 --> 05:44.593
But I didn't have a choice.

05:44.920 --> 05:47.799
His girlfriend was my inside man.

05:55.400 --> 05:57.551
And I was in love with her.

05:57.960 --> 05:59.440
(MOANING)

06:01.960 --> 06:04.680
(MOANING AND PANTING)

06:05.120 --> 06:07.112
(CHUCKLES)

06:11.400 --> 06:13.039
He'd kill her if she tried to leave him,

06:13.200 --> 06:17.513
and he'd kill us both 10 times over
if he found out we were together.

06:20.680 --> 06:23.912
But we were in love and we were stupid.

06:24.080 --> 06:27.391
And every time he was out of town,
we were together.

06:27.560 --> 06:29.472
(GIGGLES)

06:34.080 --> 06:36.117
The fit was perfect.

06:36.280 --> 06:37.760
MAN: ...get revenge on me,
when I least expect it.

06:37.920 --> 06:39.639
- You just keep saying stupid things.
- No, I don't.

06:40.160 --> 06:42.038
Yes, sir.

06:47.480 --> 06:49.472
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

06:55.000 --> 06:56.992
EMMA: I know what you like to hear
'cause I'm no fool.

06:57.320 --> 06:59.277
- (LAUGHS)
- EMMA: Like a book.

06:59.480 --> 07:00.630
Mind if I join you?

07:00.800 --> 07:03.190
Sorry, Father Time,
we're waiting for someone. (CHUCKLES)

07:03.400 --> 07:04.390
No.

07:04.560 --> 07:08.349
Emma, this is my father, Tom Coughlin.

07:09.040 --> 07:11.316
Dad, this is my friend, Emma Gould.

07:11.480 --> 07:12.675
TOM: Pleasure, Miss Gould.

07:12.840 --> 07:13.956
Mind if I sit down?

07:21.960 --> 07:23.235
Where are you from, Miss Gould?

07:23.400 --> 07:24.834
Dorchester.

07:25.920 --> 07:28.196
TOM: No, I meant before.
You're clearly Irish.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.874
All my mother's people are from Cork.

07:30.040 --> 07:32.032
Really? What's her maiden name?

07:32.200 --> 07:34.669
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

07:34.840 --> 07:37.036
She died. She's dead, my mum, so...

07:41.680 --> 07:43.478
So, what is it you do?

07:45.800 --> 07:47.871
It's a real swank place, this, isn't it?

07:49.080 --> 07:51.720
I'm aware of how my son earns a living.

07:51.880 --> 07:54.315
I can only assume that
if you've come into contact with him,

07:54.480 --> 07:56.358
it was either during a crime,

07:56.520 --> 07:59.035
or in an establishment
populated by rough characters.

07:59.520 --> 08:00.510
(MOCK LAUGHS)

08:01.680 --> 08:03.831
Are my questions
making you feel uncomfortable?

08:05.040 --> 08:07.111
I don't know what you're on about.

08:07.280 --> 08:09.556
And to be honest, I don't really care.

08:09.720 --> 08:13.111
I'm on about you being the type of
lassie who consorts with criminals.

08:13.560 --> 08:16.234
The fact that the criminal is my son
isn't the issue.

08:16.400 --> 08:18.790
It is that my son is still my son.

08:19.960 --> 08:21.917
And I have feelings that cause me

08:22.080 --> 08:24.436
to question the wisdom
of consorting with the type of woman

08:24.600 --> 08:27.069
who knowingly consorts with criminals.

08:27.480 --> 08:30.552
- Did you follow all that?
- Enough, Dad. Enough. Okay?

08:30.720 --> 08:34.679
My uncle mentioned a copper
on his payroll, name of Coughlin.

08:34.960 --> 08:36.076
Is that you?

08:38.960 --> 08:41.794
This uncle would be your Uncle Robert?

08:42.200 --> 08:44.192
Who everyone knows as "Bobo"?

08:45.120 --> 08:49.273
No, the police officer you refer to
is Elmore Conklin.

08:49.440 --> 08:51.432
He's stationed in Savin Hill.

08:51.960 --> 08:55.351
He collects shakedowns from
illegal establishments such as Bobo's.

08:55.760 --> 08:57.717
I rarely get over to Dorchester.

08:57.880 --> 08:59.155
Still, as deputy superintendent,

08:59.320 --> 09:02.757
I'd be happy to take
a greater interest in Bobo.

09:05.560 --> 09:06.960
I need to powder.

09:15.640 --> 09:17.154
Was that necessary?

09:17.320 --> 09:19.198
I didn't start the fight, Joseph.

09:19.360 --> 09:21.477
So, don't criticize me
for how I finished it.

09:23.520 --> 09:25.716
I've been a police officer for 37 years.

09:25.880 --> 09:28.634
If I've learned one thing above all,
do you know what it is?

09:28.800 --> 09:30.757
This gonna be another yarn
from the old country?

09:30.960 --> 09:32.030
No.

09:32.200 --> 09:36.194
What you put out in the world
will always come back to you.

09:36.440 --> 09:38.511
But never how you predict.

09:39.200 --> 09:40.600
I'm sure it doesn't.

09:41.080 --> 09:43.914
Unearned confidence
of that about which one is ignorant,

09:44.080 --> 09:45.639
always has the brightest glow.

09:46.840 --> 09:48.832
I think I've earned enough.

09:50.480 --> 09:52.119
She's quite easy on the eyes.

09:52.360 --> 09:53.350
(SCOFFS)

09:53.600 --> 09:54.920
Yeah, she is.

09:56.760 --> 09:59.070
Apart from that,
I fail to grasp what you see in her.

09:59.280 --> 10:00.760
Because she's from Dorchester?

10:00.920 --> 10:04.197
That doesn't help. Her father's a pimp.
Her uncle killed two men.

10:04.400 --> 10:07.234
But I could overlook all that,
Joseph, if she wasn't...

10:07.400 --> 10:09.710
She just doesn't pretend
to be something she's not.

10:10.760 --> 10:13.150
Maybe she's just asleep.

10:13.920 --> 10:15.798
Thanks for stopping by.

10:16.520 --> 10:18.193
EMMA: Maybe you should
climb under his covers tonight.

10:18.360 --> 10:19.350
JOE: What?

10:19.520 --> 10:22.035
He looks at me like I'm trash.

10:22.320 --> 10:26.109
We're not people.
We're just the Goulds from Dorchester.

10:26.280 --> 10:28.511
We tat the lace for your fucking curtains.

10:28.680 --> 10:31.400
- Jesus! You know what...
- Don't fucking touch me.

10:31.960 --> 10:34.156
My whole life,
I got the high hat and the icy mitt

10:34.360 --> 10:35.555
from people like your father.

10:36.120 --> 10:38.271
We're not less than you.

10:38.440 --> 10:39.794
I never said you were.

10:39.960 --> 10:41.280
Well, he did.

10:41.440 --> 10:44.831
Fuck him, okay? I love you.

10:47.000 --> 10:48.957
You think love's so easy.

10:51.160 --> 10:52.514
It can be.

10:56.560 --> 10:57.596
(CRYING) Oh, God.

10:59.440 --> 11:01.079
- Come here.
- I don't want to.

11:01.240 --> 11:02.230
(MUFFLED) Leave me alone!

11:02.400 --> 11:05.871
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

11:06.040 --> 11:08.999
- I want to go.
- Okay.

11:09.360 --> 11:10.510
Okay.

11:17.200 --> 11:18.759
Can you spare two bits?

11:20.400 --> 11:21.754
Thanks a lot.

11:24.200 --> 11:25.919
Joe Coughlin. I got an invitation.

11:26.120 --> 11:29.397
Put your arms up there. I gotta check you.

11:33.200 --> 11:34.190
Go ahead.

11:43.080 --> 11:44.480
Joseph?

11:44.680 --> 11:46.990
Joe Coughlin. Yeah.

11:47.280 --> 11:48.555
Pleasure.

11:50.000 --> 11:52.469
Do you know who I am?

11:52.680 --> 11:55.639
I know enough to show up here
when I'm asked.

11:57.960 --> 12:01.556
My name is Maso Pescatore.

12:03.040 --> 12:04.838
I run the North End

12:05.720 --> 12:08.235
and liquor coming up from Florida.

12:10.120 --> 12:11.634
I'm a man, uh,

12:11.800 --> 12:15.555
with the power
of other men's lives in my hands.

12:15.720 --> 12:17.359
But the truth is, uh,

12:18.880 --> 12:21.440
I'm just a simple wop
from the old country.

12:22.000 --> 12:25.789
Today, my only true rival is Albert White.

12:27.760 --> 12:30.639
When that is no longer the case,

12:30.800 --> 12:35.158
we can see an end to the fighting
that has plagued this town.

12:37.400 --> 12:40.518
Well, I got no beef with you.

12:41.760 --> 12:43.672
But I don't truck with gangsters.

12:44.120 --> 12:45.634
Not even a Sheik like you.

12:46.760 --> 12:50.231
You do soup jobs and stickups,

12:50.400 --> 12:52.357
but you're not a gangster.

12:52.520 --> 12:54.318
- What does that make you?
- I don't know.

12:54.480 --> 12:58.269
An outlaw, I guess.
I just don't want any part of that life.

12:58.440 --> 12:59.840
How many things, good or bad,

13:00.200 --> 13:04.160
come to us
whether we ask for them, or not?

13:04.400 --> 13:08.599
For example, one of my men
saw you with a young lady.

13:08.760 --> 13:11.753
Well, not so much a lady,
but a puttana moll

13:11.920 --> 13:13.718
whose daddy's Albert White.

13:18.200 --> 13:22.513
So, it no longer matters
so much what you want.

13:24.080 --> 13:25.958
You're in this life,

13:27.000 --> 13:29.276
and it can only end two ways.

13:29.440 --> 13:33.036
One, you get to Albert
and put an end to him.

13:33.200 --> 13:34.350
Two,

13:34.520 --> 13:37.399
I tell Albert about the girl.

13:37.640 --> 13:40.075
And he gets to you first.

13:42.560 --> 13:46.395
Like I said, I ain't a gangster.

13:47.400 --> 13:50.120
And I done enough killing in this life.

13:50.760 --> 13:53.355
You wanna tell your enemy
some rumor you heard? Go ahead.

13:55.240 --> 13:56.754
If I kill Albert White,

13:56.920 --> 13:59.958
somebody's just gonna jump up
and take his place.

14:00.120 --> 14:04.114
And I'd be married to the
Pescatore mob for the rest of my life.

14:05.920 --> 14:08.799
I stopped kissing rings a long time ago.

14:11.000 --> 14:12.593
Good afternoon.

14:19.040 --> 14:20.030
(DOOR CLOSES)

14:20.280 --> 14:22.033
EMMA: Do you think he told Albert?

14:22.240 --> 14:24.596
Nah. I'd be dead already.

14:24.800 --> 14:26.029
Christ.

14:27.720 --> 14:28.949
We could leave.

14:30.280 --> 14:32.033
Where would we go?

14:32.360 --> 14:33.635
Somewhere warm.

14:35.800 --> 14:38.110
My brother, Danny, lives in California.

14:38.760 --> 14:39.910
Where?

14:40.200 --> 14:42.157
I don't know.
I haven't talked to him in 10 years.

14:42.360 --> 14:45.194
He sent back a bunch of postcards
saying he was doing stunts,

14:45.400 --> 14:47.073
trying to be a writer.

14:47.280 --> 14:48.953
God, I'd go to California.

14:49.120 --> 14:51.635
I don't know much about honest work,
I gotta tell ya.

14:51.800 --> 14:53.712
- Who said anything about honest work?
- Good.

14:53.880 --> 14:56.315
No, we do what we wanna do.

14:56.600 --> 14:58.637
We'll go where we wanna go.

15:00.320 --> 15:02.676
Sleep by day.

15:06.640 --> 15:09.030
I got a job in Lawrence on Saturday.

15:09.520 --> 15:10.749
And then I'll be free.

15:10.920 --> 15:11.910
Free to leave?

15:12.080 --> 15:13.639
Yeah. Free to leave.

15:16.600 --> 15:18.796
I have to see you-know-who on Saturday.

15:18.960 --> 15:20.553
- Fuck you-know-who.
- That's the idea.

15:22.560 --> 15:23.880
Oh, come on. What's the alternative?

15:24.040 --> 15:26.600
You want me to end up in the Charles?

15:27.440 --> 15:31.354
I'm supposed to meet him
at the Statler on Saturday.

15:31.640 --> 15:34.519
Turns him on to see me
when his wife's on his arm.

15:36.400 --> 15:39.040
After that,
he's going to Detroit for a week.

15:40.720 --> 15:43.519
Can you clean yourself up
and get to the Statler by 7:00?

15:44.200 --> 15:47.352
(IMITATING ACCENT) I think I can clean
myself up and get to the Statler by 7:00.

15:47.520 --> 15:49.512
- Shut up!
- (LAUGHS)

15:52.680 --> 15:56.754
JOE: The Lawrence bank job would net us
enough to get to California on.

15:58.240 --> 16:00.118
It's true
that's what I was thinking about.

16:00.320 --> 16:01.356
(ENGINE IDLING)

16:01.560 --> 16:02.550
(DOOR OPENS)

16:06.960 --> 16:09.680
- Let's go.
- (TIRES SCREECH)

16:09.880 --> 16:11.758
- (CRASHES)
- What are you doing?

16:12.120 --> 16:13.873
- (GEAR STICK CREAKING)
- (BANK ALARM RINGING)

16:15.320 --> 16:16.879
- Copper. Copper!
- (ENGINE ROARS)

16:22.040 --> 16:23.076
(COCKS GUN)

16:25.880 --> 16:28.236
- (HONKS)
- Whoa, look out! Look out!

16:28.400 --> 16:29.914
- (TIRES SCREECHING)
- (CRASHES)

16:34.720 --> 16:35.710
- (GEAR STICK CREAKING)
- Fuck!

16:43.840 --> 16:46.071
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

16:47.080 --> 16:48.070
Get out of the way!

16:48.240 --> 16:49.230
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

16:49.480 --> 16:51.472
- (TIRES SCREECHING)
- (CAR HONKS)

16:52.920 --> 16:53.990
- Oh, fuck!
- Shit!

16:55.480 --> 16:56.470
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

16:56.760 --> 17:00.276
Move! Get out of the fucking way!
Get out of the way!

17:01.600 --> 17:02.920
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

17:03.240 --> 17:04.390
Cop!

17:18.880 --> 17:20.030
(JOE GRUNTING)

17:20.200 --> 17:21.429
(CRASHING)

17:31.120 --> 17:32.873
- All right, get out. Let's go.
- Go, go, go!

17:37.240 --> 17:39.152
Get in the car! Go!

17:57.200 --> 17:59.157
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

18:08.320 --> 18:09.310
(LAUGHS)

18:10.600 --> 18:11.716
(SHOOTING CONTINUES)

18:17.760 --> 18:18.750
Shit!

18:24.600 --> 18:26.398
(ENGINE REVVING)

18:48.480 --> 18:50.278
(TIRES SQUEALING)

18:55.880 --> 18:57.439
(CRASHING)

19:29.480 --> 19:31.915
(PANTING SOFTLY)

19:37.880 --> 19:39.633
(FIRE CRACKLING)

19:59.320 --> 20:02.358
JOE: I walked half a mile,
stole a car in North Reading,

20:02.520 --> 20:05.354
and replaced it with a Dodge
I found in Somerville.

20:05.520 --> 20:09.230
I came back to my childhood home
and considered my options.

20:14.040 --> 20:16.111
The story was in all the late editions.

20:17.040 --> 20:21.839
The third dead cop was a trooper who
pulled someone over near the state forest.

20:24.480 --> 20:26.119
Had to be Dion.

21:13.880 --> 21:15.678
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

21:50.880 --> 21:53.236
- Keep going.
- There's a service elevator up here.

21:53.400 --> 21:54.800
I can't believe you came!

21:55.000 --> 21:56.753
- What was I gonna do?
- Run.

21:56.960 --> 21:58.633
- Where?
- I don't know. It's what people do.

21:58.800 --> 22:00.075
It's not what I do.

22:05.480 --> 22:06.914
- Come on.
- (BUTTON CLICKING)

22:07.080 --> 22:08.753
Shit! Shit! Shit!

22:08.920 --> 22:10.400
(ELEVATOR DINGS)

22:20.880 --> 22:22.792
(CRYING)

22:24.840 --> 22:25.990
Why are you crying?

22:27.520 --> 22:29.000
Because I love you.

22:29.200 --> 22:30.316
Then smile.

22:31.120 --> 22:32.315
- I can't.
- (ELEVATOR DINGS)

22:33.760 --> 22:34.750
No.

22:35.720 --> 22:36.915
(GRUNTS)

22:38.800 --> 22:40.951
(GRUNTING)

22:49.800 --> 22:51.473
(GROANS)

23:00.480 --> 23:01.470
(GRUNTS)

23:05.320 --> 23:06.595
(VOMITS)

23:10.520 --> 23:12.159
(COUGHS PAINFULLY)

23:17.760 --> 23:19.479
(JOE COUGHING)

23:28.440 --> 23:32.320
I'm sure as you die,
you'll tell yourself you did it for love.

23:33.440 --> 23:34.476
No.

23:35.400 --> 23:37.869
You feel guilty about what you do,

