you may overtake our supply routes.

42:43.360 --> 42:44.476
No.

42:44.640 --> 42:47.314
I use Señor Famosa's name to reassure you

42:47.480 --> 42:49.756
that from now on,
you can work directly with me

42:50.080 --> 42:51.912
and that you can charge me a higher price.

42:52.160 --> 42:54.675
- What do we get in return?
- You get access

42:54.880 --> 42:57.759
to Ormino's cops and judges,
which we now control.

42:57.920 --> 43:00.799
And most of whom wouldn't do business
with you otherwise because you're Cuban.

43:01.160 --> 43:03.277
And you would want exclusive access
to our molasses?

43:03.440 --> 43:06.080
Nope. You just can't sell
to the White operation.

43:06.240 --> 43:08.038
Albert White is a paying customer.

43:08.960 --> 43:10.758
We've never had a problem with him.

43:10.920 --> 43:12.115
JOE: I know Albert White.

43:12.800 --> 43:15.750
I thought you might like to deal with
someone who treated you like a human being.

43:16.520 --> 43:18.716
ESTEBAN:
It is possible this will bring bloodshed.

43:18.880 --> 43:21.714
This will definitely bring bloodshed.

43:23.760 --> 43:26.514
These are very favorable terms.

43:30.040 --> 43:32.635
Albert White is what we get.

43:34.920 --> 43:37.071
JOE: The local sheriff wanted to see us.

43:37.240 --> 43:38.879
Apparently, it was a custom down there

43:39.040 --> 43:41.874
to talk about how you were gonna
break the law before you did it.

43:42.040 --> 43:43.793
What kind of guy is the chief?

43:43.960 --> 43:46.156
He's a copper, so he's an asshole.

43:46.320 --> 43:48.755
Beyond that, he's okay.

43:51.280 --> 43:53.511
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

43:53.720 --> 43:56.030
What are you doing?
Don't fuck with the guy's stuff.

43:56.200 --> 43:59.989
The sheriff's gonna come in to find some
dago going through his fucking papers.

44:03.720 --> 44:05.393
Hey, this is Figgis right here.

44:05.560 --> 44:06.880
(DOOR OPENS)

44:11.760 --> 44:12.910
Please, sit down.

44:21.560 --> 44:27.033
I won't insult you
by asking the nature of your business,

44:27.760 --> 44:31.071
so you won't have to insult me by lying.

44:32.560 --> 44:33.960
That fair?

44:34.960 --> 44:36.599
Sounds fair to me.

44:36.760 --> 44:40.037
It true you're a police captain's son?

44:40.200 --> 44:41.634
Yes, sir.

44:41.800 --> 44:43.393
You serve overseas?

44:43.560 --> 44:44.710
France.

44:45.800 --> 44:47.553
Tell it to the Marines.

44:47.720 --> 44:48.949
Yes, sir.

44:49.160 --> 44:50.879
They told it to us.

44:51.080 --> 44:53.800
I was a soldier and then a U.S. Marshal.

44:54.960 --> 44:57.236
I've killed seven men in my lifetime.

44:57.760 --> 45:01.834
Truth be told,
their faces haunt me most nights.

45:07.040 --> 45:08.315
(EXHALES)

45:09.640 --> 45:12.633
You keep your business north of 2nd,

45:12.880 --> 45:16.556
south of 27th, and east of Nebraska,

45:18.240 --> 45:21.472
you and I will have little
in the way of discord.

45:21.640 --> 45:22.630
Sounds good.

45:23.480 --> 45:25.790
I know we live in a fallen world,

45:26.920 --> 45:29.196
but just because I breathe corrupt air

45:30.640 --> 45:33.519
and rub elbows with corrupt men,

45:35.120 --> 45:39.831
never make the mistake of thinking
that I am corruptible.

45:41.040 --> 45:43.157
I won't make that mistake.

45:44.200 --> 45:45.190
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Right.

45:46.280 --> 45:49.318
Oh, dear, I'm sorry.
Thought you were alone.

45:49.480 --> 45:51.870
That's all right, Loretta.
These gentlemen were just leaving.

45:53.520 --> 45:55.159
Honey, your manners.

45:55.320 --> 45:56.720
Yes, Father.

45:58.840 --> 46:00.832
Miss Loretta Figgis.

46:01.000 --> 46:02.992
Pleased to meet you, miss.
I'm Joe Coughlin.

46:03.160 --> 46:04.355
Dion Bartolo.

46:04.520 --> 46:07.991
Loretta is taking the train
on a long journey today.

46:08.640 --> 46:10.359
It's going around.

46:10.520 --> 46:12.512
- California.
- Is that right?

46:12.680 --> 46:15.070
She's gonna be a star in Hollywood.

46:15.240 --> 46:17.675
- It's only a screen test, Daddy.
- No.

46:18.160 --> 46:22.120
A screen agent came here
and picked out a few girls.

46:23.000 --> 46:23.990
My brother's out there.

46:24.160 --> 46:26.038
Your brother's in Hollywood?

46:26.200 --> 46:27.873
JOE: He's a stuntman, I'm told.

46:28.040 --> 46:29.759
Falling off horses.

46:30.280 --> 46:31.600
Pleased to meet you, miss.

46:32.480 --> 46:33.630
JOE: Chief.

46:34.320 --> 46:35.549
Gentlemen.

46:37.200 --> 46:39.271
- You're sure you don't want a banana?
- No, that's all right.

46:39.480 --> 46:43.190
- You can't get fruit like this in Boston.
- No, I know. It looks good.

46:43.560 --> 46:45.677
- Uh-oh. Here she is.
- What?

46:45.840 --> 46:48.275
- All right. Just watch this.
- Oh, yeah?

46:51.040 --> 46:53.600
Hello. Good afternoon.

46:53.760 --> 46:55.672
- How are you?
- I'm well. How are you?

46:55.840 --> 46:57.559
Excellent.

46:57.880 --> 47:01.715
You, uh... Have you and your brother
come to any decision on our...

47:03.240 --> 47:05.550
Not yet.
We're still considering, Mr. Coughlin.

47:05.760 --> 47:06.750
Okay.

47:06.920 --> 47:09.719
Yes. It would be quite an upheaval for us.

47:09.880 --> 47:11.394
I understand. Of course.

47:11.560 --> 47:14.029
We don't make changes easily.

47:14.200 --> 47:16.590
Oh. There's all kind of change, you know.

47:16.760 --> 47:20.674
Where I was recently staying,
we used to play chess a lot,

47:20.840 --> 47:23.594
and this is the kind of change
where you get your pawn

47:23.760 --> 47:26.559
to the end of the board
and it changes into a queen.

47:26.720 --> 47:28.598
There's not a lot to think about here.

47:28.760 --> 47:31.480
- Yes. I do play chess.
- You do?

47:31.640 --> 47:33.916
Yes. My father taught me.

47:34.120 --> 47:36.794
And what you might do well to remember
is that the pawn and the king

47:36.960 --> 47:38.997
end up in the same box
at the end of the game.

47:40.280 --> 47:43.637
The end? It's not about the end.

47:43.800 --> 47:46.156
It's about when you're playing the game.

47:46.320 --> 47:49.119
You could hang me upside down
and light me on fire at the end.

47:49.280 --> 47:51.272
I wanna win while I'm playing.

47:51.520 --> 47:53.079
(CHUCKLES)

47:55.320 --> 47:57.277
I have a feeling
you win most of the games you play.

47:58.600 --> 48:00.956
Not yet. But I plan on it.

48:02.280 --> 48:04.158
Why don't you join me?

48:42.840 --> 48:45.309
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

49:11.880 --> 49:15.476
You know, some people say
liquor is only your side business.

49:15.680 --> 49:16.875
Is that so?

49:17.720 --> 49:21.600
In fact, I heard rumors
you give most of your money away.

49:21.760 --> 49:23.240
A lot of it in Cuba.

49:24.560 --> 49:26.392
And you think that's foolish?

49:26.560 --> 49:30.315
Not foolish.
It's just not my cause, that's all.

49:30.560 --> 49:32.358
What is your cause?

49:32.520 --> 49:34.751
The distribution of demon rum.

49:36.040 --> 49:39.477
And that no man should rule
another man's life.

49:41.200 --> 49:44.113
If you corner the rum market,
you will be a king.

49:45.440 --> 49:47.432
I'll still have to deal with Albert White.

49:47.600 --> 49:49.557
But how will you hold the power
once you have it?

49:50.200 --> 49:52.590
Why? You don't think I'm strong enough?

49:53.080 --> 49:55.549
I don't know if you're cruel enough.

49:57.080 --> 49:58.958
And if you are,

50:00.040 --> 50:01.440
I will be very sad.

50:01.640 --> 50:04.030
Powerful men don't have to be cruel.

50:04.760 --> 50:06.194
But they usually are.

50:08.040 --> 50:11.317
Tell me something. Do you think
there is such a thing as a noble man?

50:11.480 --> 50:13.551
I got nothing against noble men.

50:13.720 --> 50:15.632
They just rarely live past 40.

50:17.800 --> 50:19.792
My father died for Cuba.

50:20.600 --> 50:22.796
My mother died of a broken heart.

50:24.280 --> 50:27.557
He would often tell Esteban and I,
"You cannot truly live

50:27.720 --> 50:31.270
"unless there is something
for which you would die."

50:31.960 --> 50:34.759
He sounds like a good man.

50:35.320 --> 50:36.640
He was.

50:38.440 --> 50:41.080
(DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

51:32.680 --> 51:33.716
We will never be lovers.

51:34.400 --> 51:35.390
No?

51:38.360 --> 51:39.953
Why is that?

51:42.680 --> 51:44.353
We will not be lovers.

51:55.080 --> 51:56.275
(GRACIELA YELPS)

51:56.560 --> 51:58.313
(LAUGHING)

52:36.080 --> 52:38.470
(INAUDIBLE)

52:50.160 --> 52:52.914
JOE: We cornered the rum market
and lived like kings.

52:55.920 --> 52:57.240
You know what? Fine. Come on, hurry up.

53:00.280 --> 53:03.034
Banks collapsed. Jobs dried up.

53:03.240 --> 53:05.436
But vice, it seemed,

53:06.440 --> 53:08.272
was Depression-proof.

53:09.120 --> 53:10.270
Okay, let's go.

53:14.920 --> 53:18.152
JOE: The Suarez-Coughlin
partnership created a rare stability.

53:19.200 --> 53:21.396
(ALL CHEERING)

53:37.480 --> 53:39.756
We paid off Albert's guys
in Central Florida

53:39.920 --> 53:41.798
to put down their guns.

53:43.080 --> 53:47.040
So, when Albert wanted to hit us,
he had to use his Miami crews.

53:51.960 --> 53:54.156
And when they showed up,
we bushwhacked them.

53:56.240 --> 53:57.469
(SHOUTS ANGRILY)

54:00.840 --> 54:02.479
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

54:03.040 --> 54:04.793
(SLOW DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

54:13.520 --> 54:16.035
Albert was living on the run in Miami,

54:16.200 --> 54:20.558
and there wasn't a speak in Central
or North Florida we didn't sell to.

54:53.880 --> 54:55.837
Get something from in there
and put this shit out.

54:56.000 --> 54:57.070
All right.

55:00.040 --> 55:01.076
Get on the floor!

55:01.240 --> 55:02.356
- Get down, now!
- (PEOPLE SCREAM)

55:02.520 --> 55:04.989
Get on the floor. Get down!

55:05.160 --> 55:07.231
Get down! Get down!

55:10.400 --> 55:11.880
This is what happens

55:12.040 --> 55:14.509
when Catholics
try to sell liquor down here.

55:14.680 --> 55:17.036
The guy's name is RD Pruitt.

55:17.200 --> 55:19.590
Well, we'd better go find him.

55:19.760 --> 55:20.910
He's in the Klan.

55:21.080 --> 55:23.390
So, what? So are five million
other guys in this country.

55:23.560 --> 55:25.233
The Klan has a lot of fucking juice.

55:25.400 --> 55:27.471
They're inbreds
with fourth grade educations.

55:27.640 --> 55:29.074
Oh, they're gonna love you.

55:29.240 --> 55:32.631
A Catholic who works
with coloreds and lives with a Cuban.

55:32.960 --> 55:34.917
Bigger problem is RD's brother-in-law.

55:35.080 --> 55:36.070
JOE: Who's he?

55:36.240 --> 55:37.594
Chief Figgis.

55:48.600 --> 55:49.920
(DOOR OPENS)

55:53.920 --> 55:55.513
Joe Coughlin.

55:56.600 --> 55:58.193
Don't shake hands with papists.

55:59.400 --> 56:00.595
No offense.

56:00.760 --> 56:01.750
JOE: None taken.

56:02.440 --> 56:05.274
Would it help if I told you
I haven't been to church in half my life?

56:08.280 --> 56:10.192
All right, now.

56:10.360 --> 56:11.589
RD,

56:12.440 --> 56:15.274
word is you're causing trouble
down in Ybor.

56:16.640 --> 56:17.960
How's that?

56:19.600 --> 56:22.479
Well, we hear you're sticking up places.

56:23.960 --> 56:26.350
I don't know a damn thing about that.

56:27.200 --> 56:28.316
(CHUCKLES)

56:28.600 --> 56:30.478
I'm just playing with you. (LAUGHS)

56:31.640 --> 56:33.313
You all know that.

56:35.320 --> 56:36.310
RD,

56:37.480 --> 56:40.712
this is a businessman
who's come here to do business.

56:40.880 --> 56:43.918
And I suggest that you do it with him.

56:44.320 --> 56:49.315
This man is a bootlegger
and a fornicator with niggers.

56:51.640 --> 56:55.953
He needs to be tarred and feathered,
not done business with.

56:58.840 --> 57:00.035
(LAUGHS)

57:00.600 --> 57:02.273
I'm just playing.

57:02.480 --> 57:03.755
You can take a joke, right?

57:03.920 --> 57:05.149
Sure, I can take a joke.

57:05.320 --> 57:07.835
Long as you don't become one, right?

57:08.000 --> 57:09.673
(CHUCKLES)

57:12.160 --> 57:14.516
So, you like the Parisian, right?

57:14.680 --> 57:15.830
And if I did?

57:16.000 --> 57:18.993
I might be able to cut you in
on 10% of the house take.

57:19.200 --> 57:21.192
- You'd do that?
- I would.

57:21.440 --> 57:22.556
Well,

57:24.040 --> 57:26.032
I ought to be worth more than 10%.

57:26.200 --> 57:27.475
What were you thinking?

57:27.640 --> 57:29.120
I was thinking 60.

57:29.280 --> 57:30.634
JOE: 60%?

57:30.840 --> 57:32.274
The biggest club in town?

57:32.840 --> 57:33.830
That's right.

57:34.000 --> 57:35.673
For what, exactly?

57:36.360 --> 57:38.716
My friends might look on you more kindly.

57:38.880 --> 57:41.031
- What friends?
- 60%.

57:41.200 --> 57:42.953
Son, I ain't giving you 60%.

57:43.120 --> 57:46.716
I ain't your son. Ain't nobody's son.

57:46.880 --> 57:49.031
Save your father some embarrassment.

57:49.200 --> 57:51.157
- What's that?
- 15%.

57:52.680 --> 57:54.239
I will beat you to death.

57:54.400 --> 57:55.390
Excuse me?

57:56.960 --> 57:58.280
You know,

58:00.080 --> 58:03.357
that does sound like a fair arrangement.
You go to 20?

58:03.520 --> 58:07.673
I think 15's pretty good for a job
you don't have to show up to work for.

58:10.000 --> 58:13.198
Well, it's a fair deal

58:13.360 --> 58:15.556
and I'm pleased to agree to it.

58:17.200 --> 58:18.429
How do I pick up my cut?

58:18.640 --> 58:20.074
Come by the Parisian.

58:20.240 --> 58:22.436
Second Tuesday, every month, 7:00.

58:22.640 --> 58:24.233
Pleasure, Mr. Coughlin.

58:25.040 --> 58:26.190
Irv.

58:33.760 --> 58:35.274
Sounds like we have a deal.

58:35.480 --> 58:36.834
(CHUCKLES)

58:38.600 --> 58:40.956
Boy's dumb as a grape.

58:44.560 --> 58:46.233
JOE: I don't understand what Maso wants.

58:46.400 --> 58:49.996
Arrests are down 70%, revenue's up 300%.

58:50.160 --> 58:53.551
I don't like getting some kid
sent down here like we need supervision.

58:53.720 --> 58:55.439
No! We don't need supervision.

58:55.600 --> 58:58.593
Digger wants to look at the casino option,
check progress, that's all.

58:58.800 --> 58:59.995
He's gonna report back to the old man.

59:00.160 --> 59:02.436
It's a joke. Don't make a big thing of it.

59:02.640 --> 59:05.712
Maso's still gonna listen to what his son
tells him about starting a new casino.

59:05.880 --> 59:06.916
DION: Don't worry about it.

59:07.080 --> 59:08.309
How did he get the name "Digger"?

59:08.520 --> 59:09.636
Because he's a fucking dummy.

59:09.800 --> 59:12.998
All they let him do is dig ditches
for the bodies they bump off.

59:13.160 --> 59:14.560
- No shit?
- Yeah.

59:14.720 --> 59:15.710
(BOTH LAUGH)

59:17.760 --> 59:19.080
JOE: That's great.

59:19.280 --> 59:22.114
JOE: I'd come up with a plan
to invest in a casino

59:22.280 --> 59:26.240
with stakeholders in Sarasota
at the new Ritz development site.

59:27.160 --> 59:28.640
Ritz Hotel and Casino.

59:28.800 --> 59:30.280
Top shelf. A-one.

59:30.440 --> 59:31.590
...right to the casino.

59:31.760 --> 59:33.274
Absolute top-level resort.

59:33.440 --> 59:36.478
Extraordinary resort experience
whether you gamble, or not.

59:41.680 --> 59:43.239
JOE: For such a violent business,

59:43.400 --> 59:45.631
it was populated with
a surprising number of guys

59:45.800 --> 59:48.156
who were just putting food on the table.

59:48.320 --> 59:50.755
Digger wasn't one of those guys.

59:53.680 --> 59:55.000
So, this is it.

59:55.160 --> 59:57.311
Volstead Act won't last forever, right?

59:57.480 --> 59:59.949
What are we gonna do
when Prohibition ends?

01:00:00.120 --> 01:00:01.110
Gambling.

01:00:01.320 --> 01:00:03.596
We use the connections
we put together to get it legalized.

01:00:03.760 --> 01:00:05.672
And we're the only ones in place
to run it.

01:00:05.840 --> 01:00:07.160
And this is it?

01:00:07.320 --> 01:00:09.039
JOE: It will be. Ritz Longboat Key.

01:00:09.200 --> 01:00:11.157
I sat down with the owners
in Sarasota last week.

01:00:11.320 --> 01:00:12.640
Why did they let us in?

01:00:12.800 --> 01:00:15.031
Because they can't get gambling legal,
and they can't run a casino.

01:00:15.200 --> 01:00:18.796
They own the property, we run the casino.
We chop the profits 50-50.

01:00:18.960 --> 01:00:20.519
Wait a minute.

01:00:20.720 --> 01:00:23.474
Do we have a magic stick
for changing laws?

01:00:23.680 --> 01:00:24.955
I heard you got bingo legal.

01:00:25.520 --> 01:00:26.636
(LAUGHS)

01:00:26.840 --> 01:00:28.718
It's a step. It's that prerequisite.
You gotta do one thing,

01:00:28.880 --> 01:00:30.712
- and then you get...
- Yeah, I know. It was a prerequisite.

01:00:30.880 --> 01:00:32.678
Your grandmother can come down.
She'll play in the church.

01:00:33.800 --> 01:00:34.995
Bingo!

01:00:35.560 --> 01:00:39.793
Look, I got bagmen buying inspectors
in Tallahassee and Sarasota.

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:43.032
I got guys going after senators
and IRS agents who gamble.

01:00:43.240 --> 01:00:47.154
We get gambling legal, we are rich. Legit.

01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:49.630
For the long fucking haul.

01:00:50.160 --> 01:00:51.992
I talk a good game, too.

01:00:53.080 --> 01:00:54.230
But I like you.

01:00:55.080 --> 01:00:56.309
(CHUCKLES)

01:00:57.240 --> 01:00:59.038
He's a very smart boy.

01:01:01.480 --> 01:01:04.234
JOE: Maso went crazy for the casino.

01:01:04.400 --> 01:01:07.916
Called every day for updates
like it was his idea.

01:01:19.480 --> 01:01:21.278
(LAUGHING)

01:01:25.200 --> 01:01:27.271
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

01:01:38.120 --> 01:01:41.955
It was addressed to
"Sir Joseph Coughlin, nigger fucker."

01:01:42.600 --> 01:01:44.796
Inside, was a two-word note,

01:01:44.960 --> 01:01:46.713
"Sixty percent."

01:01:49.800 --> 01:01:51.632
(PEOPLE SCREAM)

01:01:56.480 --> 01:01:58.073
(SCREAMING)

01:02:04.320 --> 01:02:07.154
Same note. Same message.

01:02:18.120 --> 01:02:20.999
We're doing everything we can,
but he's protected.

01:02:21.160 --> 01:02:23.152
His roots here are too deep.

01:02:23.320 --> 01:02:25.915
Well, time to start digging.

01:02:28.040 --> 01:02:30.760
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

01:02:37.120 --> 01:02:39.999
VIRGIL: Afternoon, gentlemen.
Virgil Beauregard.

01:02:40.160 --> 01:02:41.992
What can I do for you today?

01:02:45.080 --> 01:02:47.800
We're hoping you can talk
some sense into RD Pruitt.

01:02:48.160 --> 01:02:51.119
Ain't too many people
ever had much success doing that.

01:02:51.840 --> 01:02:53.433
We'd like you to try.

01:02:53.600 --> 01:02:55.273
And what would the reason be?

01:02:55.440 --> 01:02:56.794
His self-preservation.

01:02:57.000 --> 01:02:59.151
He needs to stop shooting up my clubs.

01:02:59.880 --> 01:03:01.200
Clubs?

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:04.640
What kind of clubs? Bridge clubs?

01:03:04.840 --> 01:03:08.197
Because I belong to
the Greater Tampa Rotary Club myself,

01:03:08.360 --> 01:03:10.158
and I don't recall ever seeing you.

01:03:11.680 --> 01:03:13.876
I come here
to do a piece of business with you,

01:03:14.040 --> 01:03:15.633
and you wanna play fucking games?

01:03:15.800 --> 01:03:18.110
- Is that what I wanna do?
- Look,

01:03:19.160 --> 01:03:21.550
you're the Grand Wizard
of the Ku Klux Klan around here.

01:03:21.720 --> 01:03:23.120
Congratulations.

